PRECIOUS METALS : Futures prices eased as increased stability and strength came into the securities markets . 
December_DATE delivery gold fell $_MONEY 3.20_MONEY an ounce to $_MONEY 377.60_MONEY . 
December_DATE silver declined 6.50_MONEY cents_MONEY an ounce to $_MONEY 5.2180_MONEY . 
January_DATE platinum was down $_MONEY 5.70_MONEY an ounce at $_MONEY 494.50_MONEY . 
Precious metals , gold in particular , currently are being influenced more by stock market gyrations than the dollar as traders seek greater investment stability , according to William_PERSON O'Neill_PERSON , vice president of research at Elders_ORGANIZATION Futures_ORGANIZATION in New_LOCATION York_LOCATION . `` The recent rally in precious metals was a result of uncertainty and volatility in equities , '' he said . 
Yesterday , the stock market rose strongly , creating a more defensive attitude among precious metals traders , he said . 
Silver and platinum , which have more of an industrial nature than gold , were even weaker , he said . 
Silver is also under pressure of `` extremely high '' inventories in warehouses of the Commodity_ORGANIZATION Exchange_ORGANIZATION , he said . 
Yesterday , these stocks rose by 170,262 ounces to a record of 226,570,380 ounces , according to an exchange spokesman . 

COPPER : Futures prices partially recovered Monday_DATE 's declines because Chilean miners voted to strike . 
The December_DATE contract rose 1.20_MONEY cents_MONEY a pound to $_MONEY 1.14_MONEY . 
In Chile_LOCATION , workers at two copper mines , Los_LOCATION Bronces_LOCATION and El_LOCATION Soldado_LOCATION , which belong to the Exxon-owned Minera_ORGANIZATION Disputada_ORGANIZATION , yesterday voted to begin a full strike tomorrow , an analyst said . 
Reasons for the walkout , the analyst said , included a number of procedural issues , such as a right to strike . 
The analyst noted that also inherent in all metal markets was a sympathetic reaction to stocks . 
In the case of copper , he said , the upbeat mood of stocks was reflected in demand for futures contracts because a stronger economy means greater buying interest for the metal . 
Also contributing to the firmness in copper , the analyst noted , was a report by Chicago_LOCATION purchasing agents , which precedes the full purchasing agents ' report that is due out today and gives an indication of what the full report might hold . 
The Purchasing_ORGANIZATION Management_ORGANIZATION Association_ORGANIZATION of_ORGANIZATION Chicago_ORGANIZATION 's October_DATE index rose to 51.6_PERCENT %_PERCENT after three previous months of readings below 50_PERCENT %_PERCENT . 
The September_DATE index was 47.1_PERCENT %_PERCENT . 
A reading below 50_PERCENT %_PERCENT generally indicates a slowing in the industrial sector of the economy , while a reading above 50_PERCENT %_PERCENT points to expansion . 
The Chicago_LOCATION report raised the possibility that the October_DATE survey of the National_ORGANIZATION Association_ORGANIZATION of_ORGANIZATION Purchasing_ORGANIZATION Management_ORGANIZATION would also show a reading above 50_PERCENT %_PERCENT . 

